Description

Public competition at the City of Mendrisio.

Location: Car mechanics or mechatronics 100%.

Dicastery Institutions and resources Administrative Section Stationery Via Municipio 13 6850 Mendrisio 058 688 31 10 stationary@mendrisio.ch Ris. mun. 4803 of 21.04.2026 24 of April 2026 Competition for the recruitment of a mechatronic or a mechatronic of 100% car at the Environment and infrastructure Division of the City of Mendrisio

Shipments

- management and maintenance of vehicles and equipment of the Environment Division and infrastructure at the mechanical workshop of municipal warehouses;
- cooperation in all areas of relevance to the external teams of the Environment and Infrastructure Division;
- execution of manual and technical works also outdoor and in different climatic conditions;
- collaboration is also required in the winter service, such as clearing snow and spreading of ice salt;
- availability to provide service even outside ordinary working hours, including urgent interventions;
- availability to follow specific training courses also outside canton.

In addition:

- Other work assignments compatible with its function and its competences may be or are given to it;
- It can be called or called to provide service at irregular times even out of time on public holidays according to service requirements.

Requirements

- Federal certificate of capacity (AFC) such as mechatronics or automotive mechatronics;
- driving license category “B”;
- good knowledge of the Italian language;
- physical fitness for the performance of the planned tasks;
- reliability, sense of responsibility, operational autonomy and teamwork.

City of Mendrisio

They may be preferential requirements:

- professional “C” driving license;
- multiannual experience;
- skills in electronic diagnostics;
- knowledge of hydraulic systems and tyres.

What we offer

- Yearly wage (threeteenth monthly and salary scale updated at 01.01.2026):
- Classes (4*) 5 – 7 ROD (Operation/A Artisan Function);
- Minimum: CHF 62,022.-- annually (*CHF 58’371.--);
- Maximum: CHF 85'327.-- annual;
- In addition to the salary, the allowance for children according to LAFam is paid.
- Working week: 40 hours
- Degree of employment: 100%
- Start of activities:
- From 1 June 2026 or date to be agreed.
- The first year of service is considered as a test year.

Contact and Expiry

- Applications must be submitted via the application form by Friday 15.05.2026 at 23:59, accompanied by the following documents:
- Letter of motivation;
- Curriculum vitae with photos;
- Copy certificates of study, work and improvement;
- Self-certification on good conduct (available from the site of the Municipal Administration of Mendrisio);
- Questionnaire on the state of health for the recruitment of personnel to the dependencies of the City of Mendrisio (available from the site of the Municipal Administration of Mendrisio).
- Applications submitted in another form will not be considered.
- This notice of competition and its application form are also available on the https://www.mendrisio.ch/concourses.
- The Human Resources Section remains at the courteous disposal (tel. +41 58 688 33 10) of those who do not have a device (PC, tablet, smartphone, scanner, etc.) to provide them with the necessary tools to send their application through the prescribed application form.
- In addition to the documents to be attached to the application, at a later time may be required to present the extract of the judicial box and the extract of the execution register (validity 6 months).
- The City Hall reserves the right to change the tasks at any time, in relation to any changes in the regulations and provisions of service in force.
- It is the faculty of the City Hall to proceed with a pre-selection of candidates and candidates for the call to hearings.
- The City Hall reserves the right not to proceed with recruitment, in the absence of candidates or candidates eligible for the function.
- Legal remedies: Within 30 days of the date of publication, the appeal shall be made to the Lodevole Council of State.
- More information: Detailed information can be obtained from the Environment and Infrastructure Division of the City of Mendrisio, Via F. Zorzi 1, Mendrisio, tel. 058 688 34 40.

Registration deadline

2026-05-15.

