Description

Public competition at the City of Mendrisio.

Location: Installer or 100% electrician installer with fontaniere function.

Dicastery Institutions and resources Administrative Section Cancelleria Via Municipio 13 6850 Mendrisio 058 688 31 10 stationary@mendrisio.ch Ris. mun. 4787 of 21.04.2026 24 of April 2026 Competition for the recruitment of an Installer or an Electricist Stallator at 100%, indeterminate time, at the municipal font (AIMpio)

Shipments

- to collaborate in the phase of study, implementation and commissioning of new aqueduct plants;
- co-ordinate the ordinary maintenance of drinking plants and aqueduct infrastructure in accordance with the provisions of self-control provided by Swiss food legislation;
- operate as a reference person for fault management, ordinary maintenance and improvement interventions regarding telemanagement and electrical installations;
- keep the documentation inherent to the plants per day;
- provide availability to participate in the regular picket service;
- coordination and management activities.

In addition:
- other work assignments compatible with its function and its skills may be given to it;
- can be called/to provide service at irregular times, even out of time and on public holidays according to service requirements.

Requirements

- Federal capacity certificate (AFC) such as Electrical Installer or Installer;
- diploma of Fontaniere or Fontaniera AFP or availability to achieve it;
- experience in industrial automation systems or aqueduct telemanagement;
- experience in aqueducts can be preferential title;
- good knowledge of MS Windows operating system and its MS Office tools;
- proven experience in the management of teams;
- good relational, organizational, communicative and analytical skills;
- licence to conduct category B;
- knowledge of a second national language (German or French) are preferential title;
- Swiss citizenship or home in Switzerland.

What we offer

- gross annual salary (threeteenth monthly and salary scale updated at 01.01.2026):
- Classes (7)* 8 - 10 ROD (Cooperator/administrative/a function);
- Minimum: CHF 72’975.-- annually (*CHF 69’324.--);
- Maximum: CHF 100’867.-- annual;
- in addition to the salary is paid, to the entitled persons, the allowance for children according to LAFam.
- Working week: 40 hours
- Degree of employment: 100%
- Start of activities:
- As soon as possible.
- The trial period is extended until the APF of fontaniere (art. 9 cpv 2, ROD).

Deadline and Application Mode

- Applications must be submitted via the application form by Friday 15 May 2026 at 23:59, accompanied by the following documents:
- presentation letter;
- curriculum vitae with photos;
- copies of certificates of study and work;
- self-certification on good conduct (available from the site of the Municipal Administration of Mendrisio);
- questionnaire on the state of health for the recruitment of personnel to the dependencies of the City of Mendrisio (available from the site of the Municipal Administration of Mendrisio).

- Applications submitted in another form will not be considered.
- This notice of competition and its application form are also available on the https://www.mendrisio.ch/concourses.
- The Human Resources Section remains at the courteous disposal (tel. +41 58 688 33 10) of those who do not have a device (PC, tablet, smartphone, scanner, etc.) to provide them with the necessary tools to send their application through the prescribed application form.
- In addition to the documents to be attached to the application, at a later time it may be required to present the extract of the judicial box for individuals and the extract of the execution register (validity 6 months).
- The City Hall reserves the right to change the tasks at any time, in relation to any changes in the regulations and provisions of service in force.
- It is the faculty of the City Hall to proceed with a pre-selection of candidates and candidates for the call to hearings.
- The City Hall reserves the right not to proceed with recruitment, in the absence of candidates or candidates eligible for the function.

Legal remedies

Within 30 days of the date of publication, the appeal shall be made to the Lodevole Council of State.

More information

Detailed information can be obtained from the Directorate AIM, Via Municipio 13, Mendrisio, tel. 058 688 38 00.

Registration deadline

2026-05-15.

